37
00:02:37,070 --> 00:02:38,710
They're doing a fine work.

38
00:02:39,169 --> 00:02:42,939
But scaling this to a
complicated system often fails.

39
00:02:43,439 --> 00:02:49,219
And coding agents, while they can
pretty easily index a given repo or a

40
00:02:49,219 --> 00:02:53,369
small set of repos, what's known as a
workspace, this doesn't scale very well

41
00:02:53,379 --> 00:02:57,600
or very easily to a larger system, right?

42
00:02:58,100 --> 00:03:02,310
The gist of the answer usually
lies in providing the right

