00:17:30,429 --> 00:17:32,799
analyzing what's going on in the system.

249
00:17:33,489 --> 00:17:39,129
It has different tools to access
logs, to query logs, to access Jira

250
00:17:39,139 --> 00:17:41,369
tickets Slack messages, et cetera.

251
00:17:41,829 --> 00:17:46,589
But it also uses the architecture hub
to find out more information about the

252
00:17:46,589 --> 00:17:51,289
system's architecture and guided where
to look information or what information

253
00:17:51,289 --> 00:17:53,179
to look in other places as well.

254
00:17:53,679 --> 00:17:57,199
Like I said, we have different
query skill variants.

255
00:17:57,249 --> 00:18:01,589
The difference, the main difference is
the ability to run the query locally

256
00:18:01,589 --> 00:18:07,949
if you have a local copy of the local
clone of the architecture hub, or the

257
00:18:07,949 --> 00:18:13,319
ability to leverage Git-based tools
like GitHub command line interface or

258
00:18:13,329 --> 00:18:18,669
GitHub MCP tools to read in places where
you don't have it cloned, so you can

